body:
Heh I can certainly see why it is made like that ðŸ™‚ 

This is a one stop of a scroll with an external mouse:

```
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseWheel { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))), delta: LineDelta(0, 1), phase: Moved } }
```

And this is one stop of a scroll with touchpad:

```
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseWheel { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))), delta: LineDelta(0, 0.040570177), phase: Moved } }
```

I wonder if you have a general idea how to normalize values coming from touchpad?

----

It is also surprising that scrolling with mouse produces way more WindowEvents than scrolling with a touchpad. 

Mouse, full list of events for one scroll stop:


```
glutin event: DeviceEvent { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(18))), event: Motion { axis: 3, value: -15 } }
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseWheel { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))), delta: LineDelta(0, 1), phase: Moved } }
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseEntered { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))) } }
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseLeft { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))) } }
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseEntered { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))) } }
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseLeft { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))) } }
```

Touchpad:

```
glutin event: DeviceEvent { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(13))), event: Motion { axis: 3, value: -0.6085526316892356 } }
glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(65011715))), event: MouseWheel { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(2))), delta: LineDelta(0, 0.040570177), phase: Moved } }
```
